-- Seed: platform-owned account + 1st Contact marketing site.
-- The seed embeds the file-backed site.json snapshot from
-- sites/1stcontact/site.json so D1-backed and file-backed paths converge.
-- Both draft_definition and published_definition point at the same snapshot;
-- a published_revision_id records the publish-flow pointer for symmetry.
--
-- Insertion order: accounts -> sites -> revisions.
-- revisions.site_id has a declared FK to sites(id); sites.published_revision_id
-- is a soft pointer (no FK declared) so it can be set before the revision row
-- exists without violating constraints.

